Given its long history, one would think mail is a well-documented material, but that is not the case. For the first time, this books lays a solid foundation for the understanding of mail armour and its context through time. It applies a long-term multi-dimensional approach to extract a wealth of as yet untapped information from archaeological, iconographic and written sources. This is complemented with technical insights on the mail maker’s chaîne opératoire.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 03. Jan 2023) 0aArmiesxHistoryyTo 1500zEurope. 0aMilitary uniformsxHistoryyTo 1500. 4aAntiquity. 4aArchaeology. 4aArt and Material Culture. 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 4aMedieval Studies. 7aANTIQUES & COLLECTIBLES / Military.2bisacsh  amulti-dimensional approach to material culture, development and transition of technology military equipment long-term: Iron Age - Roman period - Middle Ages.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074322708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Library and Information Science 2021 Englishz978311075410008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Library and Information Science 2021z9783110753875oZDB-23-DGB40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048554294?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048554294423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048554294/original  a978-3-11-074322-7  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021